Preposition
για • (gia)

(time, duration, takes acc.): for

(conj) so, then, therefore, consequently; (interjection) se, well, then, now then, now [λοιπόν] OR (adj) remaining, left over, rest, remainder, (pl.) others [ λοιπός ]

εισιτήριο • (eisitírio) n (plural εισιτήρια)
(transport, theater) ticket for bus, train, etc, or theatre, etc
δεν -- not (with stress on the negative aspect of a statement)
(interj.) please/you're welcome (interro) can I help you?/excuse me?/hello?

indicates subjunctive, imperative; converts to noun phrase
to, indicates subjunctive, imperative; converts to noun phrase

place (an area; somewhere within an area)
